<item>
            <title>[OPENJPA-1906] Issue info / warning message when connection retain mode is always</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OPENJPA-1906</link>
                <project id="12310351" key="OPENJPA">OpenJPA</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Many users see better performance when setting openjpa.ConnectionRetainMode to always. But they might not be aware of the consequences - the EntityManager must be closed in order to release the connection. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the case of application managed entity managers, the application should always close the EntityManager when it&apos;s done. But since this may or may not be obvious, it&apos;s a good idea to log an info message. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the case where the application cannot directly close the EntityManager (e.g. a Container Managed EntityManager), we should log a warning to let users know that each EntityManager may hold on to a connection for a long time. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Unfortunately we can only detect whether the EMF is container managed, not the EM - but some warning is better than none. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
